        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 2:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 200 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Villa Grove, or 55 miles east of Gunnison, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texas Creek, Coaldale, Cotopaxi, Villa Grove, and Hillside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for central
Colorado.</instruction>
